---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
import Eyebrow from '../../components/Eyebrow.astro';

const updated = 'June 2026';
---

<Layout
  title="Privacy Policy"
  description="Privacy policy of Frido's Friends e.V. under the GDPR: data controller, hosting, self-hosted fonts, donations via betterplace.org, no cookies, no tracking tools."
  lang="en"
  path="/en/privacy"
  spine="none"
>
  <section class="section">
    <div class="container-text">

      <header class="section-head" data-reveal>
        <Eyebrow text="Legal" />
        <h1>Privacy Policy</h1>
        <p class="lead" style="margin-top:var(--sp-4)">
          Protecting your data matters to us. This website collects as little data as
          possible: no cookies, no tracking tools, no advertising networks. Below we
          explain what data is nonetheless processed and what rights you have.
        </p>
      </header>

      <div class="legal-body prose">

        <h2>1. Data Controller</h2>
        <p>
          The party responsible for data processing on this website within the meaning of the
          General Data Protection Regulation (GDPR) is:
        </p>
        <p>
          <strong>Frido&rsquo;s Friends e.V.</strong><br />
          Gemarkenstraße 12<br />
          51069 Köln<br />
          Germany
        </p>
        <p>
          Email: <a class="link-tertiary" href="mailto:martin.hirt@cassandra.ceo">martin.hirt@cassandra.ceo</a>
        </p>

        <h2>2. Hosting</h2>
        <p>
          This website is hosted by Netlify, Inc. (512 2nd Street, Suite 200, San Francisco,
          CA 94107, USA). The transfer of data to the USA is safeguarded by Netlify&rsquo;s
          participation in the EU-US Data Privacy Framework (DPF); on this basis, an adequate
          level of data protection applies to the transfer.
        </p>
        <p>
          When the website is accessed, technically necessary data is processed in so-called
          server log files — in particular the IP address, information about your browser and
          operating system, and the timestamp of the request. This processing is required for
          the secure and stable operation of the website. The legal basis is Art. 6(1)(f) GDPR
          (legitimate interest in the technically error-free provision of the website).
        </p>

        <h2>3. Fonts</h2>
        <p>
          The fonts used on this website are loaded exclusively from our own server
          (self-hosted). There is <strong>no connection to external font providers</strong> and
          therefore no transfer of your data to third parties. This is a privacy advantage for
          you: when the fonts load, neither your IP address nor any other data is transmitted to
          a third-party provider.
        </p>

        <h2>4. Donations via betterplace.org</h2>
        <p>
          For donations and membership contributions we use the donation platform betterplace.org,
          operated by the non-profit betterplace.org gGmbH. When you donate via betterplace.org,
          the data you enter there is processed by betterplace.org gGmbH as an independent data
          controller. The privacy policy of betterplace.org applies in this respect. Please
          inform yourself there about the nature, scope and purpose of the data processing before
          you enter your data.
        </p>

        <h2>5. Cookies and Tracking</h2>
        <p>
          This website sets <strong>no cookies</strong> and uses <strong>no analytics or
          tracking tools</strong>. There is no web tracking, no usage profiles are created, and
          no advertising networks are integrated.
        </p>

        <h2>6. Contacting Us by Email</h2>
        <p>
          If you contact us by email, we process the data you provide (your email address and the
          content of your message) solely to handle your request. The legal basis is Art. 6(1)(f)
          GDPR (legitimate interest in responding to your enquiry) or Art. 6(1)(b) GDPR, where
          your enquiry relates to a contract or a membership. We do not pass this data on without
          your consent and delete it as soon as it is no longer required for the stated purpose.
        </p>

        <h2>7. Your Rights</h2>
        <p>
          Within the scope of the statutory requirements, you have the right at any time to:
        </p>
        <ul>
          <li>access the data stored about you (Art. 15 GDPR),</li>
          <li>rectification of inaccurate data (Art. 16 GDPR),</li>
          <li>erasure of your data (Art. 17 GDPR),</li>
          <li>restriction of processing (Art. 18 GDPR),</li>
          <li>data portability (Art. 20 GDPR).</li>
        </ul>
        <p>
          To exercise these rights, an informal message to
          <a class="link-tertiary" href="mailto:martin.hirt@cassandra.ceo">martin.hirt@cassandra.ceo</a>
          is sufficient.
        </p>

        <h2>8. Supervisory Authority</h2>
        <p>
          You have the right to lodge a complaint with a data protection supervisory authority
          about the processing of your personal data. The authority responsible for us is:
        </p>
        <p>
          <strong>State Commissioner for Data Protection and Freedom of Information
          North Rhine-Westphalia (LDI NRW)</strong><br />
          Kavalleriestraße 2&ndash;4<br />
          40213 Düsseldorf<br />
          Germany
        </p>

        <p class="legal-stand caption">As of: {updated}</p>

        <p class="legal-back">
          <a class="link-tertiary" href="/en/imprint">To the imprint &rarr;</a>
        </p>
      </div>

    </div>
  </section>
</Layout>

<style>
  /* Page-local layout for the legal reading column — tokens only, no new globals. */
  .legal-body h2 {
    margin-top: var(--sp-8);
    margin-bottom: var(--sp-4);
    padding-top: var(--sp-5);
    border-top: 1px solid var(--line);
  }
  .legal-body h2:first-of-type { margin-top: var(--sp-6); }

  .legal-body ul {
    margin: 0 0 var(--sp-4);
    padding-left: var(--sp-5);
  }
  .legal-body li { margin-bottom: var(--sp-2); }

  .legal-stand { margin-top: var(--sp-8); }

  .legal-back {
    margin-top: var(--sp-5);
    padding-top: var(--sp-5);
    border-top: 1px solid var(--line);
  }
</style>
